replies.bodyText:
@opusforlife2 I agree with you about censorship. We are not in a position - either ethically or scientifically - to decide which content is good or bad, true or false, to be looked at or preferred, or not to be viewed. I am aware of the problematic that arises when opening not all instances is supported or worse, when some instances are deliberately blocked. Pornography was only one example, which immediately caught my eye by the URL. The question is whether we simply support opening all instances. We are in no way responsible for their content and users should be aware of it because they already got the URL.
They main problem I see, when adding all 449 instances, is crashing old devices, or at least create lags. Every shared URL would be checked against 449 patterns for PeerTube and some others for YouTube (+ invidio + hooktube), SoundCloud, mediaCCC. And that's only for NewPipe. I should have communicated that clearer.
For this reason, I suggested to only add a few instances to the manifest. We can add more on request or even ask our users in a blog post for their most used instances. Adding the most popular for now does not prevent us from adding unknown or small instances later.
